BES sees good performance in 1997 . Portuguese bank Banco Espirito Santo expects to post a good performance in 1997 but it will be hard to maintain profit growth of around 20 percent , BES ' s president Ricardo Espirito Santo Salgado said . " It is natural that we will continue to grow well , " he told Reuters . " We believe that 1997 will also be a good year . " He added : " But to maintain profit growth of around 20 percent would be very difficult . We cannot predict such a level of profit growth . " Salgado was speaking after the bank announced a 21 . 3 percent increase year - on - year in its 1996 profit to 23 . 59 billion escudos . 
